text: Moingona is an unincorporated community in Boone County, in the U.S. state of Iowa. ==History== Moingona got its start in 1866, when the Chicago and Northwestern Railroad was extended to that point. The community derives its name from the Moingona Indians. A post office was established at Moingona in 1867, and remained in operation until it was discontinued in 1928. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Boone County, Iowa Category:Unincorporated communities in Iowa
title: Moingona, Iowa
